				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I guess you could have a CPU only working with basic MOVE instructions, mapping the ALU in memory. It would only need additional hardware to process conditionals.<br />This was done on x86, see <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R7EEoWg6Ekk" class="postlink">here</a>.<br />Of course there are many considerations on how to design the CPU in order to know which instructions you need (eg. do you need a JMP instruction, or is PC accessible like General Purpose Registers so only MOV is required, see ARM CPUs where you can access PC like any other register if I recall correctly).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

