					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I feel like you have a fully functional CPU if you have the following in it:<br /><br />1- logical NAND and/or NOR (Sheffer's Stroke!)<br />2- Load<br />3- Store<br />4- Jump if Zero<br /><br />4- Add (optional for convenience).<br /><br />Don't quote me but I think that's all it takes to make your CPU an universal Turing machine.</div>

					
